name: The Perfect Brew
description:

Everyone has their own special way of making the perfect cuppa, be it a builders brew or without milk. This graphic print celebrates the British tradition of the perfect brew - a great addition to any kitchen!

Open edition digital print, supplied unframed and printed on 310gsm Hahnemühle German etching paper. (Image shows print in black frame. Frame not included).

name: Personalised Prints
description:
Create a completely unique print!  Jen Pringle's personalised prints make a beautiful gift for that someone special. Using names or initials together with original mixed media graphics, we create a bespoke and very personal piece of art that reflects your loved one's personality and passions.

To create your unique personalised print, we send you a brief asking you for a list of 3 key things that either represent the person the print is for or 3 things they love. Each print is then individually created and emailed as a proof for you to approve before printing. A proof is normally sent within 3 - 5 days of accepting your order.

Jen Pringle's Personalised Prints are the perfect gift for anniversaries, birthdays or any other special occasions, and is a guaranteed winner for that person who has just about everything.

50cm x 70cm, digitally printed on 310gsm Hahnemühle German etching paper and supplied unframed. Signed by the artist. A personalised message card is also available to send with your commissioned print for the perfect finishing touch.

Each print is carefully rolled in white tissue paper and posted to you in a robust cardboard tube to ensure safe delivery.

name: Personalised Prints for Little Ones
description:

To create your unique personalised print, we ask you for a list of 3 key things that either represent the person the print is for or 3 things they love along with any preferred colour choices. Each print is then individually created and emailed as a proof for you to approve before printing. A proof is normally sent within 3 - 5 days of accepting your order.
